tooltip.add_images_to_default_group: Automatically add workspaces to default group when new workspaces are added.
tooltip.agent_version: This setting is used to restrict which versions of the Kasm Agent are allowed to communicate with the Manager.
tooltip.anonymous_user_expiration: If configured, anonymous user accounts will be automatically deleted after this amount of time specified in hours.
tooltip.api_private_key: Private Key used to sign request between Kasm components.
tooltip.api_public_cert: Public key used by Kasm components to validate internal API calls.
tooltip.auto_agent: Automatically enable an agent when it calls in.
tooltip.debug_retention: Number of hours to retain local Kasm debug logs. WARNING - See Kasm documentation before adjusting.
tooltip.default_cpu_allocation_method: Sets the default cpu allocation strategy for container images. Valid options are Quotas or Shares.
tooltip.default_vm_rdp_connection_settings: Default connection settings for VM RDP sessions.
tooltip.default_vm_ssh_connection_settings: Default connection settings for VM SSH sessions.
tooltip.default_vm_vnc_connection_settings: Default connection settings for VM VNC sessions.
tooltip.enable_kasm_auth: Require client requests to the Kasm for content such as downloads and uploads to be authenticated with the user's current session token.
tooltip.forward_inter_zone_agent_requests: When contacting Agents in a different zone, forward requests through the alternate Zone's proxy address.
tooltip.guardian_interval: The number of seconds between the Manager API inspection of existing Agent, and Kasm availability.
tooltip.guardian_provision_threads: The number of threads the Manager API server uses for teardown and provision tasks.
tooltip.hec_token: The Splunk HEC token used for authentication of logs to a Splunk server.
tooltip.host_dead_expiration: The number of seconds since an Agent's last check-in before marking it as dead. Dead servers are automatically destroyed if they were dynamically provisioned.
tooltip.host_missing_expiration: The number of seconds since an Agent's last check-in before marking it as dead.
tooltip.http_method: HTTP method to use, valid values are post and put. Splunk uses POST while ElasticSearch API uses PUT
tooltip.https_insecure: Set to true if the remote logging server does not have a valid signed cert by a public certificate authority.
tooltip.kasm_auth_domain: Override the domain used in the Kasm session cookie.
tooltip.keepalive_expiration: Clients regularly send keepalive requests when logged into a Kasm. This value is the number of seconds a Kasm will remain active after the last keepalive is received.
tooltip.launcher_background_url: Url used to specify the background image for the launcher.
tooltip.license_server_url: The URL to the Kasm Licensing Server.
tooltip.log_host: The hostname or IP address of the remote logging server, not applicable for internal logging.
tooltip.log_port: The port to use for logging communication.
tooltip.log_protocol: The logging protocol used, allowed values are internal, https, splunk, and elasticsearch
tooltip.log_retention: Number of days to retain local Kasm logs. WARNING - See Kasm documentation before adjusting.
tooltip.login_assistance: Enables a Login Assistance link on the login page to the entered URL. Not shown if value is empty.
tooltip.manager_expiration: The number of seconds until the manager is considered permanently unavailable, at which time the manager record will be removed from the database. A value of 0 disables the expiration check.
tooltip.max_login_attempts: The number of invalid login attempts before an account is locked out. This setting only applies to local accounts.
tooltip.minimize_local_logging: When using a remote logging solution like Splunk, minimize local database logging for better scalability.
tooltip.primary_manager_timeout: The number of seconds until the primary manager is considered unavailable. If other managers are alive one will take over the primary role.
tooltip.provision_timeout: The maximum amount of time to wait for auto-scaled VMs to check-in and become available. After this time is exceeded, the VM is automatically destroyed.
tooltip.registration_token: Token used to self-register new components to the deployment.
tooltip.same_site: Configures the SameSite attribute for the Set-Cookie HTTP response headers. Valid options are Lax, Strict and None.
tooltip.same_zone_reply: If set to true, a manager will only reply to agent heartbeats with a list of managers in the same zone as itself. Otherwise a list of all managers is given. This allows Agents to failover to managers in other zones.
tooltip.session_lifetime: The number of seconds a session token is valid for.
tooltip.token: An authentication token used in the communication between Kasm Agents and the Manager API server.
tooltip.token_drift_max: How many minutes should a TOTP token be allowed to drift.
tooltip.update_check: This Setting will stop the manager from checking for Kasm system updates.
tooltip.url_endpoint: The Splunk endpoint, most likely /service/collector/event. For ElasticSearch it would be index/_doc/.
tooltip.cleanup_orphaned_autoscale_servers: If the system is interrupted or errors during AutoScaling a server can be partially provisioned and the system may lose track of the server orphaning it. This consumes resources that the system cannot provision on. Enabling this setting allows the system to use heuristics to find and destroy orphaned resources.
tooltip.web_filter_update_url: Url used to updated the Web Filter Categorization database
